# App release metadata (apps/user)

The home page footer displays version and deploy date from a **single source of truth**:

`apps/user/lib/app-release.ts`

## Mandatory on every production deploy

When preparing a deploy of **apps/user** (Vercel / production), you **must** update that file in the **same PR or commit** as the deploy:

1. **`APP_VERSION`** — bump semver (`1.0.1` → `1.0.2` for routine releases)
2. **`APP_RELEASE_DATE`** — set to deploy date in **Asia/Bangkok**, format **`YYYYMMDD`** (e.g. `20260701`)

Do **not** duplicate version/date in `page.tsx`, env vars, or package.json for the footer.

## When to apply

- User asks to deploy, release, or ship to production
- PR touches `apps/user` and is intended for production
- Completing a feature batch that will go live on Vercel

## Verification

Before finishing, confirm:

- [ ] `APP_RELEASE_DATE` matches today in Bangkok (unless user specified another deploy date)
- [ ] `APP_VERSION` was incremented from the previous deploy
- [ ] Footer still imports from `@/lib/app-release` only
